message:
Thank you for the wonderful insight on the subtleties of using async/await. Quick question about async/await and entity framework methods like ToListAsync(), FirstOrDefaultAsync() and so on when they are used in the context of ASP.NET:

public class FooController: Controller  
{  
 [HttpGet]  
 public ActionResult SomeAction() => View("SomeView", new SomeViewModel  
 {  
 PingPong = new SomeRepository().GetSomething() //sync  
 });  
}

public class SomeRepository  
{  
 public int GetSomething()  
 {  
 return _context.SomeTable.FirstOrDefaultAsync(x => ...).Result;  
 }  
}

Will the above piece of code deadlock due to the direct use .Result?

Please accept my apologies if I'm missing something obvious here and thank you again for your insights.
